National Daily can confirm that Manchester United have sanctioned their agreement to sign Lisandro Martinez from Ajax.
The transfer of the Argentina international has remained a priority for the Old Trafford club after the 24-year-old declared his interest to join his former boss in the Premier League.
The arrival of Martinez will see United complete their third transfer under Ten Hag
The arrival of the talented defender will bring United’s transfer under new boss Erik ten Hag to three after the arrival of Tyrell Malacia from Feyenoord and Christian Eriksen as a free agent after his short-term stay with Brentford.
Ajax have confirmed that United will pay €57.37million for the Argentina international – with that fee to rise €67.37m through variables National Daily gathered.
